.TH NEOSC_UTIL_BASE64_DECODE 3  2015-04-10 "" ""
.SH NAME
neosc_util_base64_decode \- decode base64 string
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <libneosc.h>
.sp
.BI "int neosc_util_base64_decode(char *in, int ilen,"
.BI "                             unsigned char *out, int *olen);"
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR neosc_util_base64_decode()
function decodes a string in base64 format to an output array. The output length must be at least 75% the size of the input length. The "olen" parameter must contain the output buffer size on input and contains the actual output length on function return.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.BR neosc_util_base64_decode()
function returns zero in case of success and -1 in case of any error.
